OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Joe Randall
OL,5,FAdvanced landing grounds were often
OL,6,Fconstructed using tarred canvas,
OL,7,Fmatting and metal mesh and sometimes
OL,8,Fthe dust proved a problem for many
OL,9,Faircraft.
OL,11,F"It was really hard work" he said.
OL,13,F"We had to dig in every night to get
OL,14,Fout of sight. We had one blanket. If
OL,15,Fit rained that was hard luck. You got
OL,16,Fup in the morning and you never took
OL,17,Fany clothes off. Boots and everything
OL,18,Fwere on because we weren't that far
OL,19,Fback. To me being as young as it was I
OL,20,Faccepted it more than the other chaps.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/6
